# Filters, Sorting & URL State — Reusable Architecture

## Overview

All tables with filters + sorting follow the same pattern:

1. **URL as source of truth** — filters, sorting, search, pagination all live in URL params.
2. **Backend does the filtering/sorting** — frontend never filters in memory.
3. **Reusable components** — `FilterDrawer`, `FilterFieldMultiSelect`, `FilterFieldRange` from `src/components/filter-drawer/`.
4. **Page-specific URL hook** — one hook per entity that defines its schema.

---

## Filter Drawer — `src/components/filter-drawer/`

### When to use

Any table that has more than just a search input needs filter fields. Use the drawer pattern instead of inline filter rows.

### Components

```tsx
import {
  FilterDrawer,
  FilterFieldMultiSelect,
  FilterFieldRange,
} from 'src/components/filter-drawer';
```

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `FilterDrawer` | Trigger button + MUI Drawer container |
| `FilterFieldMultiSelect` | Multi-select Autocomplete with checkboxes |
| `FilterFieldRange` | Two number inputs (min / max) |

### Usage pattern

```tsx
<FilterDrawer
  filtersCount={activeFiltersCount}      // drives the error badge
  title={tx('common.actions.filters')}
  resetLabel={tx('common.actions.reset')}
  onReset={resetFilters}                 // clears all filters + resets page
>
  <FilterFieldMultiSelect
    label={tx('products.filters.category')}
    options={categories.map((c) => ({ value: c.id, label: c.name }))}
    value={categoryIds}                  // string[] parsed from URL
    onChange={(ids) => setFilters({ categories: ids.join(',') })}
  />
  <FilterFieldRange
    label={tx('products.filters.quantityRange')}
    minLabel={tx('products.filters.minQty')}
    maxLabel={tx('products.filters.maxQty')}
    minValue={minQuantity}
    maxValue={maxQuantity}
    onMinChange={(v) => setFilters({ minQuantity: v })}
    onMaxChange={(v) => setFilters({ maxQuantity: v })}
  />
</FilterDrawer>
```

### Rules

- `filtersCount` must count only **active** (non-empty) filters — drives the badge.
- `onReset` must clear all filter URL params AND reset `page` to 1.
- Range inputs → debounce before sending to API query (see URL state pattern below).
- Multi-select → update URL immediately on change.

