## URL State Hook — per-entity pattern

Each entity with advanced filters gets its own URL state hook in `api/use-<entity>-url-state.ts`.

### Defining the schema

```ts
// Outside the hook — stable reference, no useMemo needed
const ENTITY_URL_SCHEMA = {
  page: intParam(1),
  page_size: intParam(15),
  search: stringParam(''),
  ordering: stringParam('-created_at'),
  // Comma-separated IDs for multi-select
  categories: stringParam(''),
  // Range filters stored as strings
  min_quantity: stringParam(''),
  max_quantity: stringParam(''),
} as const;
```

Key rule: **define the schema object at module scope**, not inside the hook. This prevents `useUrlQueryState` from re-subscribing on every render.

### Array params — comma-separated strings

Multi-select filters are stored as comma-separated strings in the URL:

```
?categories=id1,id2,id3
```

Parse in the hook:
```ts
const categoryIds = useMemo(
  () => (categories ? categories.split(',').filter(Boolean) : []),
  [categories]
);
```

Serialize when sending to backend:
```ts
// In the request function:
...(params.categoryIds?.length ? { categoryIds: params.categoryIds.join(',') } : {}),
// humps converts camelCase key → snake_case: categoryIds → category_ids
```

### setFilters — always resets page to 1

```ts
const setFilters = useCallback(
  (patch: EntityFilterPatch) => {
    setValues({
      categories: patch.categories ?? categories,
      min_quantity: patch.minQuantity ?? minQuantity,
      max_quantity: patch.maxQuantity ?? maxQuantity,
      page: 1,  // always reset
    });
  },
  [setValues, categories, minQuantity, maxQuantity]
);
```

### Debounce range inputs in the view

URL updates immediately (shareable, bookmarkable). API call fires only when user stops typing:

```ts
const debouncedMinQty = useDebounce(minQuantity, 400);
const debouncedMaxQty = useDebounce(maxQuantity, 400);

useProductsListQuery({
  minQuantity: debouncedMinQty || undefined,
  maxQuantity: debouncedMaxQty || undefined,
});
```

