## Reusing for a New Entity (e.g. Clients, Sales)

1. **Create `use-<entity>-url-state.ts`** — define the URL schema with `intParam`/`stringParam`, expose `setFilters`, `resetFilters`, `activeFiltersCount`.

2. **Add backend filters** — extend `get_queryset()` in the ViewSet with `filter(field__in=[...])` / `filter(field__gte=n)`.

3. **Add `ordering_fields`** — include every column users will sort.

4. **In the view** — plug `FilterDrawer` + fields + `handleSort` + `useDebounce` for text range inputs.

5. **Export** (optional) — add `export-excel` action + request function + `useMutate` hook; pass current filter params.

---

## Quick Reference

| Task | Where |
|---|---|
| URL state for all filters | `api/use-<entity>-url-state.ts` |
| Reusable drawer trigger + panel | `src/components/filter-drawer/filter-drawer.tsx` |
| Multi-select filter field | `src/components/filter-drawer/filter-field-multi-select.tsx` |
| Range filter field | `src/components/filter-drawer/filter-field-range.tsx` |
| Parse ordering string → (orderBy, order) | `useMemo` in view (see pattern above) |
| Backend multi-category filter | `get_queryset()` + `filter(category_id__in=[...])` |
| Backend range filter | `get_queryset()` + `filter(field__gte=n)` |
| Export respects current filters | `filter_queryset(get_queryset())` in action |
